At the scene, police found a 32-year-old man with laceration wounds. The victim was later rushed to hospiptal for treatment, but was later discharged. Two men have been arrested in connection with the attack, a 23-year-old on suspicion of grievous bodily harm and a 19-year-old on suspicion of affray. The victm of the stabbing has also been arrested on suspicion of affray, Affray is also known as a breach of the peace. British Transport Police have subsequently asked for any witnesses to the attack or for anyone with any information to come forward. If you have anything to report you can get in touch by texting 61016 or calling 0800 40 50 40 quoting reference 714 of 13/01/23. Alternatively, you can call Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.